title: NZ Elections Explained
text: New Zealand non-compulsory voting voters electing 120 members unicameral House Representatives using mixed-member proportional (MMP) voting system. system: 7 seats Māori electorates reserved people Māori ethnicity ancestry choose place separate electoral roll. Māori General electorates overlap. 48 members elected nationwide, closed (.e., order candidates determined individual parties), party lists (List MPs). separation Māori General electoral roll voters List MPs. means voters cast two votes election day: one vote local candidate electorate (Candidate Vote) second vote party (Party Vote). Party Candidate votes can explored using summary dataset national-level. number type seats can also viewed using dataset.

title: NZ Elections Explained
text: national level, 120 seats allocated parties proportional number votes party received Party Vote. number electorates won subtracted number remaining seats distributed party’s allocation (top-). order seats allocated determined using Sainte-Laguë formula: \[ quotient = \frac{V}{2s + 1} \] : \(V\) total number votes party received, \(s\) number seats allocated far party. detailed explanation allocation process can found Seat Allocation Explained article. electorate-level Party Vote data, view party_votes dataset.

title: NZ Elections Explained
text: FPTP results can accessed candidate_votes dataset electorate-level (NB. candidate_votes dataset currently contains successful parties , unsuccessful parties grouped ‘’). type electorate (Māori General) can also identified using add_type function. addition, majority dataset lists winner electorate (.e., Candidate Vote), majority, margin victory/marginality. majority calculated using following formula: \[ Majority = candidate_{1} - candidate_{2} \] : \(candidate_{1}\) number votes first candidate received, \(candidate_{2}\) number votes second candidate received. margin victory, denoted \(MoV\), calculated using following formula: \[ MoV = \frac{Majority}{n} \] : \(n\) total valid votes cast electorate candidates.

title: Seat Allocation Explained
text: First, Party Votes tallied party number electorate seats won also tallied.
code: # load dataset df <- scgUtils::get_data("summary") df <- df %>%   # filter out total ballot type, leaving the candidate and party ballor   # types only   filter(Ballot != "Total",          # filter for the most recent election          Election == 2023) %>%   # keep party votes only by removing candidate votes   mutate(Votes = ifelse(Ballot == "Candidate", 0, Votes),          # NB % is not required in this step and is only included          # for illustrative purposes          Percentage = ifelse(Ballot == "Candidate", 0, Percentage),          # keep the number of electorate seats only by removing          # party/list seats          Seats = ifelse(Ballot == "Party", 0, Seats)) %>%   # group long format data frame (NB keep 'Successful' column)   group_by(Party, Successful) %>%   summarise(Votes = sum(Votes), Percentage = sum(Percentage),             Seats = sum(Seats), .groups = 'drop') %>%   ungroup() %>%   arrange(-Votes)  head(df) #> # A tibble: 6 × 5 #>   Party          Successful   Votes Percentage Seats #>   <chr>          <chr>        <dbl>      <dbl> <dbl> #> 1 National Party Yes        1085851      38.1     43 #> 2 Labour Party   Yes         767540      26.9     17 #> 3 Green Party    Yes         330907      11.6      3 #> 4 ACT Party      Yes         246473       8.64     2 #> 5 NZ First       Yes         173553       6.09     0 #> 6 Maori Party    Yes          87844       3.08     6

title: Seat Allocation Explained
text: Next, ineligible parties (achieve 5% Party Vote win least 1 electorate) removed denominator total votes. percentage party votes recalculated seat entitlement number top-seats determined.
code: df <- df %>%   # filer out ineligible parties   filter(Successful == "Yes") %>%         # New percentage   mutate(Percentage = Votes/sum(Votes)*100,          # Number of seats each party is entitled to          Entitlement = round(120 * Percentage/100, digits=0),          # Number of top-up seats          Top_Up = Entitlement - Seats) head(df) #> # A tibble: 6 × 7 #>   Party          Successful   Votes Percentage Seats Entitlement Top_Up #>   <chr>          <chr>        <dbl>      <dbl> <dbl>       <dbl>  <dbl> #> 1 National Party Yes        1085851      40.3     43          48      5 #> 2 Labour Party   Yes         767540      28.5     17          34     17 #> 3 Green Party    Yes         330907      12.3      3          15     12 #> 4 ACT Party      Yes         246473       9.16     2          11      9 #> 5 NZ First       Yes         173553       6.45     0           8      8 #> 6 Maori Party    Yes          87844       3.26     6           4     -2

title: Seat Allocation Explained
text: Next, Sainte-Laguë formula, \(Quotient = \frac{Votes}{(2s + 1)}\), used determine order seats. NB \(s\) begins 0 Party increases 1 seats allocated round. means total number \(Votes\) party divided odd number every round. .e., \((2 \times 0 + 1) = 1\) \((2 \times 1 + 1) = 3\) \((2 \times 2 + 1) = 5\) …
code: n <- 120 # Total number of seats: df1 <- data.frame() # s begins at 0 and sequences up until total number of seats # has been reached for(s in seq(0,n)) {     tmp <- df %>%       # Saint-Lague Formula:       mutate(Quotient = Votes / (2*s + 1),              # included for illustrative purposes only              s = s) %>%       select(Party, Quotient, s)     df1 <- rbind(df1, tmp) } head(df1,10) #> # A tibble: 10 × 3 #>    Party          Quotient     s #>    <chr>             <dbl> <int> #>  1 National Party 1085851      0 #>  2 Labour Party    767540      0 #>  3 Green Party     330907      0 #>  4 ACT Party       246473      0 #>  5 NZ First        173553      0 #>  6 Maori Party      87844      0 #>  7 National Party  361950.     1 #>  8 Labour Party    255847.     1 #>  9 Green Party     110302.     1 #> 10 ACT Party        82158.     1

title: New Zealand Election Data Explorer
text: scgElectionsNZ R package provides data functions exploring New Zealand’s general election results. data elections occuring 1996 2023, unless stated otherwise. package provides following datasets: summary: overall results national-level party turnout: turnout informal vote electorate ballot type (candidate party) vote_type: valdidity vote type electorate ballot type (candidate party) party_votes: party vote electorate party (electorate-level) candidate_votes: candidate vote electorate party (electorate-level) majority: winning candidate margin victory electorate (electorate-level) split_total: split-ticket voting (2005 - 2023 ) - number voters cast party vote different party candidate vote (national-level party) preMMP_results: overall results 1890 1993 (prior introduction MMP) (national-level party) historic_turnout: turnout 1879 2023 (national-level year)
